qas.question: The Autopista AP-53 was originally built by whom?
Name another road they responsible for.

context: Within Galicia are the Autopista AP-9 from Ferrol to Vigo and the Autopista AP-53 (also known as AG-53, because it was initially built by the <a0_0>Xunta de Galicia<a0_0/>) from Santiago to Ourense. Additional roads under construction include Autovía A-54 from Santiago de Compostela to Lugo, and Autovía A-56 from Lugo to Ourense. The Xunta de Galicia has built roads connecting comarcal capitals, such as the aforementioned AG-53, Autovía AG-55 connecting A Coruña to Carballo or <a1_0>AG-41<a1_0/> connecting Pontevedra to Sanxenxo.
